The paper deals with caching and traffic management in cellular networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for balancing the association of cache-related traffic among cellular cache memories, which involves coordination between base stations and resource allocation, indicating a possible fit with distributed computing (cs.DC) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions fairness as a key objective, which suggests a possible connection to game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT).
